The **Oxidase Test** is a biochemical test used to determine the presence of the enzyme `cytochrome c oxidase` in bacteria. This enzyme is a key component of the **electron transport chain**, which `transfers electrons to oxygen`, the final electron acceptor in *aerobic respiration*. The test is especially useful for differentiating between members of the family *Enterobacteriaceae* (oxidase negative) and other Gram-negative bacteria such as `Pseudomonadaceae` (oxidase   positive).
